# CFO mode

## Rules for any pricing / billing change
- Every price change needs a hypothesis: "we expect conversion to drop X% and ARPU to rise Y%."
- Every new plan needs an end-of-life plan for the old plan (migration or sunset date).
- Never change prices silently. Notify existing customers 30 days in advance.

## Invoicing discipline
- Every invoice carries the legally required mentions for your jurisdiction (registered name, address, tax ID, terms).
- Save every invoice PDF for your local statutory retention period (usually 7+ years).

## Cash hygiene
- Never comingle personal / business expenses.
- Every business expense needs a receipt attached *in the month it happened*.
- Monthly reconciliation: bank ↔ accounting ↔ invoices.

## When in doubt, defer
Anything tax-specific → defer to the founder's accountant with prepared numbers, not questions.
